### Critical: this repo's working copy

The REAL working copy is `~/Development/EvairSIM-App`.
`~/Library/Mobile Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/EvairSIM-App-Backup` is a RSYNC MIRROR, not the working copy. Never edit files there — they get overwritten on next save.

Reason: `flutter create` / `pub get` hangs inside iCloud Drive (fake-IP / VPN pub.dev resolution). Local-only path is mandatory.

## One command saves everything (both projects)

```bash
bash "/Users/jordanmok/Desktop/iCloud Drive/Cursor Codes/save-all.sh"
# or with a custom commit message:
bash "/Users/jordanmok/Desktop/iCloud Drive/Cursor Codes/save-all.sh" "feat: xyz"
```

## Save just this project (Flutter)

```bash
bash "$HOME/Development/EvairSIM-App/scripts/save.sh"
# or with a custom commit message:
bash "$HOME/Development/EvairSIM-App/scripts/save.sh" "feat: xyz"
```

`scripts/save.sh` will:
1. `git add -A && git commit -m "<msg>"` (skipped if no changes)
2. `git push origin <branch>`
3. `git push aliyun <branch>:feature/evairsim-jordan` — **never touch `feature/pccw` (China team's branch)**
4. `rsync` working tree → iCloud backup (excluding `.git`, `.dart_tool`, `build`, iOS/Android build artifacts)
5. Exit non-zero if any step fails

## When to auto-save

Save after any of these, without asking:
- Any code change lands
- The user says "save", "save my work", "commit", "push"
- A feature/milestone is done
- A bug fix is verified
- Before ending a session

## Aliyun push policy

